en's basketball|Clemson]],[[Xavier Musketeers men's basketball|Xavier]], [[NC State Wolfpack men's basketball|NC State]], [[Miami Hurricanes men's basketball|Miami (FL)]], [[Penn Quakers men's basketball|Penn]],<ref name=villanova /> [[Penn State Nittany Lions men's basketball|Penn State]], [[Temple Owls men's basketball|Temple]], [[UMass Minutemen basketball|UMass]], and [[Villanova Wildcats men's basketball|Villanova]].<ref name=signature /> He signed to play for Villanova in late November 1996.<ref name=signature /> As a true freshman at Villanova, O'Connor found little playing time under coach [[Steve Lappas]], starting 5 out of 21 games, and scoring a season-high 12 points against Temple.<ref name=nba>{{Cite web|url=http://archive.nba.com/draft2002/profiles/marvin_oconnor.html|title=Marvin O'Connor|website=[[NBA.com]]|year=2002|access-date=April 13, 2020}}</ref> At the end of the season he had averages of 4.7 points, 1.7 rebounds and 1.2 assists per game.\n\nAfter the end of his first season at Villanova, O'Connor decided to transfer to [[Saint Joseph's Hawks men's basketball|Saint Joseph's]].<ref name=nba />\n\n===College statistics===\n{{NBA player statistics start}}\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | [[1997\u201398 NCAA Division I men's basketball season|1997\u201398]]\n| align=\"left\" | [[1997\u201398 Villanova Wildcats men's basketball team|Villanova]]\n| 21 || 5 ||  || .354 || .217 || .357 || 1.7 || 1.2 || 0.5 || 0.0 || 4.7\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[1998\u201399 NCAA Division I men's basketball season|1998\u201399]]\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[1998\u201399 Saint Joseph's Hawks men's basketball team|Saint Joseph's]]\n| colspan=11 align=center | ''Did not play \u2013 transfer''\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | [[1999\u20132000 NCAA Division I men's basketball season|1999\u201300]]\n| align=\"left\" | [[1999\u20132000 Saint Joseph's Hawks men's basketball team|Saint Joseph's]]\n| 28 || 28 || 31.5 || .408 || .354 || '''.736''' || '''4.4''' || '''2.6''' || '''1.1